/Ronde-pairjpg-768x532.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-1536x1063.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-2048x1417.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-218x150.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 218w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-696x482.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-1068x739.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-1920x1329.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-607x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 607w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164032/Ronde-pairjpg-100x70.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 100w\"><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-253584\">The Parcours Ronde wheels are aerodynamically optimized to work with 28mm tires.</figcaption></figure><p>As you might imagine, these road wheels are optimized for wide tires. In this case, Parcours says the Ronde wheels are best paired with 28mm tires.</p><p>The Ronde wheels take a similar approach to Parcours’ Strade wheels — wider is better. But the Ronde wheels feature a shallower rim profile. Whereas the Strade wheels feature a 49.2mm depth up front and 54mm in the rear, the Ronde hoops drop down to a 35.6mm depth up front and 39.3mm in the rear.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub.jpg\" alt=\"Alloy hubs\" width=\"2400\" height=\"2400\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2400px) 100vw, 2400px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub.jpg 2400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-800x800.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-768x768.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-1536x1536.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-2048x2048.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-696x696.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-1068x1068.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-1920x1920.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-420x420.jpg 420w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub.jpg 2400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-297x297.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-800x800.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-120x120.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-768x768.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-1536x1536.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-2048x2048.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-696x696.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-1068x1068.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-1920x1920.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164539/ronde-hub-420x420.jpg 420w\"></p><p>Both front and rear wheels feature a 22.5mm internal rim width. Parcours says that the rims are optimized for 28mm tires, but they still offer aero benefits for tires up to 32mm. According to Parcours, it would be possible to run 700c tires up to 50mm wide on the Ronde wheels.</p><p>Despite the growing popularity of hookless rims, Parcours has opted for a hooked rim that’s compatible with both standard clincher or tubeless tires.</p><p>Alloy hubs with “high-grade EZO cartridge bearings” round out the package. Best of all, this 1,400-gram wheelset costs $1,400 — far less than some of its carbon competition.</p><h2>Ronde wheels go wide for a reason</h2><figure id=\"attachment_253586\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-253586\"><img load