oads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup.jpg 2400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-297x232.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-800x624.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-120x94.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-768x599.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-1536x1198.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-2048x1597.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-696x543.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-1068x833.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-1920x1498.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164308/ronde-closeup-538x420.jpg 538w\"><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-253586\">The Ronde rims accommodate standard clincher or tubeless tires.</figcaption></figure><p>It wasn’t too long ago that the idea of wide wheels and tires had the road world balking. But going wider allows riders to run lower tire pressures, which in turn leads to a wider contact patch. This reduces rolling resistance, increases traction, and improves ride quality.</p><p>The Ronde wheels go wide because of that common knowledge, and they are so named because wider wheels and tires tend to create a much dreamier ride — something that comes in handy on things like the Flandrien cobbles of the Spring Classics.</p><h2>Aero optimization</h2><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM.png\" alt=\"Data comparison chart\" width=\"1596\" height=\"900\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1596px) 100vw, 1596px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM.png\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM.png 1596w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-297x167.png 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-800x451.png 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-120x68.png 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-768x433.png 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-1536x866.png 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-696x392.png 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-1068x602.png 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164629/Screen-Shot-2021-03-24-at-1.59.44-PM-745x420.png 745w\" srcset=\"