oads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-265x198.jpg 265w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile.jpg 2400w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-800x600.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-120x90.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-1536x1152.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-2048x1536.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-1920x1440.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/24164438/ronderim-profile-265x198.jpg 265w\"></p><p>According to a Parcours white paper, the Ronde wheels beat out the Grimpeur Disc wheels, as well as Enve’s 3.4AR wheels and Zipp’s 303S wheels in the A2 Wind Tunnel in North Carolina. (The Ronde wheels beat its competitors in a yaw angle from 2 to 8 degrees.)</p><p>The Ronde wheels tout 46.1 grams of drag (total wheelset aero drag) versus 46.6 grams of drag from its nearest competitor, the Enve 3.4AR wheels. In other words, when paired with a 28mm tire, these wheels are darn fast according to A2’s wind tunnel data. Of course, Parcours does mention that the aerodynamic benefits begin to diminish at tire widths over 32mm.</p><p>The Ronde wheels are available now on <a href=\"https://www.parcours.cc/products/ronde\">Parcours.cc.</a></p></div></div>","author":"Dan Cavallari","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2f471dc10e1b4d717da1db5d983b98749093f4c67848f42aa73b35d671e04f7b","category":"Cycling"}